RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 9700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 2, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 2, 2022 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALL ME JELLY ROLL drew quickly clear and rated a long lead, was hand urged away from the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and dug in under steady stretch handling. CREEDIBILITY saved ground on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, circled rivals in the five path of the far turn and came along to take second late yards. UPSY DAISY DO saved ground off the pace on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. MOONLIGHT MISS ducked out and made contact with. UNEXPECTEDLY leaving the gate and rounded the first turn about the four path, left the turn outside, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced two deep on the far turn and showed little in the lane. The latter was bumped leaving the gate, raced in the four path on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. TINA'S SONG settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened inside the eighth pole. FONDA ROMANA steadied at the start and raced in the three path the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, weakened into the far turn and was eased in the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Tina's Song
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,chased past 1/2,rail far turn,weakened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Call Me Jelly Roll
ENTRY.COMMENT: quickly clear,rated long lead,hand urged turn,steadily handled

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUSTINUPISHARDTODO chased and raced close off the rail on the turn, took the lead inside the eighth pole, ran clear toward mid-stretch and was steadily handled to widen. BODYSLAM chased the early pace toward the outside, raced in the three path on the turn, eased out leaving the turn and dug in to take second late yards. BUY HERE PAY HERE set a pressured pace and contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, was met leaving the eighth pole and flattened later yards. TAKE AIM gave chase, raced two deep on the turn, finished evenly and just missed third. DANNY'S WINKSTER gave chase inside, rounded the turn at the rail and ran evenly in the lane. SCREAMING JEREMY gave chase and raced in the five path on the turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 62. Claiming Purse 13800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibi lity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAVANGER settled off the rail on the first turn, eased out leaving the second turn and bid approaching the seven sixteenths pole, took over toward the three eighths and kept the edge over Dakota Boy through the backstretch, drew clear nearing the quarter, dug in under steady stretch encouragement and just lasted. TYRY TYRANNOSAURUS settled off the pace about the three path, bid past the seven sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn in the three path, dug in leaving the turn and just missed. HERETODAYGONMANANA saved ground well off the early pace, started a bid toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and came along for third inside the sixteenth pole. LIGHTNING LAD rounded the opening turn about the four path then steadied off the inside flank of Tyry Tyrannosaurus approaching the seven eighths pole, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths, raced in the five path of the far turn and showed little in the lane. DAKOTA BOY moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the seven sixteenths pole, was met nearing the three eighths and gave chase from that point, but dropped back into the far turn and weakened in the lane. AMERICAN ROCKY raced off the pace inside on the first turn, rounded the second turn in the four path, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn at the rail and weakened in the lane. DOMINANT FACTOR raced in the five path the first turn and never factored. LIL TOUGHMAN rated close off the rail early on, gave chase passing the half mile pole then faded through the far turn. The Stewards reviewed, then dismissed, a claim of foul against the rider of Tyry Tyrannosaurus for alleged interference in the vicinity of the seven eighths pole, lodged by the rider of Lightning Lad.

ENTRY.NAME: American Rocky
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace inside,4p 2nd turn,chased 7/16,rail far turn,weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace 3p,bid 7/16,3p far turn,finished well,just missed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 16900. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRUE HEIRESS chased inside and raced close off the rail on the turn, dug in to match strides with CAPTAIN SAM and inched ahead of that one through the final yards, while the latter was hustled to the front approaching the seven sixteenths pole and set a pressured pace, rounded the turn at the rail, was met mid-stretch and grudgingly relented the final yards. GARY DOING BIZ broke through prior the start, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path and ran evenly down the lane. DEEMED ESSENTIAL became a bit anxious in the gate then gave chase outside, rounded the turn in the five path and passed rivals through the lane. CLEARLY VISIBLE gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. MS HEADLEY had a brief early lead, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded into the turn. SCARLET TANAGER gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and weakened in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 19400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races W here Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JEFFERSON SECURITY was a bit reluctant to load but took the lead approaching the three quarter pole, moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the three eighths pole, edged clear of BERNIE THE GAMBLER midway on the far turn and was steadily handled to hold on. The latter rounded the opening turn about the four path then stalked into the backstretch, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced close in the three path on the far turn and dug in through the stretch to maintain second. FELICIAS CASTLE raced wide on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and finished well at the outside girth of Bernie The Gambler. S S ALASKAN CRUZ raced off the rail on the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and ran evenly in the stretch. WINDSOR'S TRACKER stalked the early pace from the two and three paths, challenged toward the three eighths pole but dropped back off the rail midway on the far turn and flattened inside the eighth pole. ORANGEBURG was shuffled back early and raced in the five path the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, ran in the four path of the far turn then flattened stride. MADDEYE MOODY rated close inside, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and weakened. YDOUHAVETOBESOMEAN rounded the first turn about the six path and showed little response through the backstretch. MIO GRACELAND raced off the rail on the first turn then faded through the backstretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 44. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWESOME MOON chased through the backstretch and raced close in the three path of the turn, dug in for the lead nearing mid-stretch and dueled clear later yards. IMINCHARGENOW pressured the pace three wide, took the nod approaching the quarter pole but was met approaching mid-stretch and relented later yards. JACKYSINTHECASTLE chased the early pace inside, raced near the rail on the turn but angled to the outside toward the head of the lane and finished strong to take third the final yards. KEY TO THE CASTLE chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, was forced outward toward the head of the lane but ran evenly in the lane. SHOWTHEMONEYHONEY chased toward the inside, raced at the rail on the turn, was eased outward toward the head of the lane, lost momentum off the heels of ONLY ROMANCE at the eighth pole then flattened the final sixteenth. The latter pressured the pace two deep but dropped back off the rail midway on the turn and weakened in the lane. BOWMANS LAZY GIRL set a pressured pace, was met approaching the quarter pole and weakened leaving the turn. TIMES CHANGED FOLLOWING REVIEW.

ENTRY.NAME: Iminchargenow
ENTRY.OWNER: Ali Andrew and Schottroffe Edward T

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 2 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY CHARLIE entered the first turn in the six path and raced close into the backstretch, challenged at the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from the five sixteenths, raced two deep most of the far turn, bore out approaching the top of the lane but dug in for the lead mid-stretch and drew clear late yards. MAKE THE WAY CLEAR rated close to the early pace inside but dropped back at the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and dug in to take second under the wire. JOHNNY SWISH rated close off the rail then closed to the lead approaching the three eighths pole, was met a dueled at even terms from the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn at the rail, relented the final sixteenth and was nipped from second under the wire. MONEYFORNOTHING entered the first turn about the five path and settled off the pace, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened in the four path of the far turn. REVERE NOTE contested the early pace then showed the way from the five eighths pole, came under pressure nearing the seven sixteenths, was met toward the three eighths and faded through the backstretch. BELMULLET rated close three wide on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole and weakened at the rail on the far turn.
